      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:3:4:84:23",
      "text": [
        " سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) عَنْ أَفْضَلِ سَاعَاتِ الْوَتْرِ فَقَالَ الْفَجْرُ أَوَّلُ ذَلِكَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Al-Husayn Bin Muhammad Al-Ashary, from Abdullah Bin Aamir, from Ali Bin Mahziyar, from Fazalat Bin Ayoub, and Hammad Bin Isa, from Muawiya Bin Wahaba who said, ",
          "‘I asked Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> about the most superior of the timings for Al-<span class=\"iTxt\">Witr</span>. So he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘The dawn is the beginning of that’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "23. Al-Husayn ibn Muhammad al-Ash’ariy has narrated from ‘Abd Allah ibn ‘Amir Ali ibn Mahziyar from Fadalah ibn Ayyub and Hammad ibn ‘Isa from Mu‘awiyah ibn Wahab who has said the following: “I once asked abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, about the most excellent time for al-Witr. He (the Imam) said, ‘Dawn is the beginning of it.” "
        ]
      }
